The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Lanka to tour Bangla in Nov.
Dhaka: Sri Lanka will play two Tests and three ODIs on their first tour of Bangladesh later this year, officials said on Tuesday. The Sri Lankans will begin the three-week tour with two day-night ODIs in Dhaka on November 10 and 11, followed by the third ODI in Chittagong on November 14. Chittagong will also host the first Test from November 18, while the second will be played in Dhaka from November 25. Bangladesh, now under former Sri Lanka coach Dav Whatmore, are currently touring the West Indies. THE ITINERARY Nov. 10: First ODI (D/N) in Dhaka. Nov. 11: Second ODI (D/N) in Dhaka. Nov. 14: Third ODI in Chittagong. Nov. 18-22: First Test in Chittagong. Nov 25-29: Second Test in Dhaka.  (AFP)  Copyright 
